com.tozny.e3db

Class SearchRequest

  • Object
    • com.tozny.e3db.SearchRequest

  • public class SearchRequest
extends Object
    Holds all parameters for an E3DB query operation.

    This class allows you to specify all parameters for performing a Search against E3DB (using the Client.search(SearchRequest, ResultHandler) method). Instances of this class must be created using the SearchRequestBuilder class.

    By default, queries are limited to 50 records, only return records written by the calling client, and results do not include the data associated with each record (only the Record.meta() portion). See the SearchRequestBuilder class for documentation about configuring these parameters.

    Given an instance of this class, you can use the buildOn() method to create a SearchRequestBuilder that is pre-configured to the values held by the SearchRequest instance. This makes pagination easy to implement, where the nextToken parameter is the only thing that needs to vary.

    Behavior with Multiple Filters

    SearchRequest supports both match and exclude filters. For additional configuration concerns see SearchParams.

    Getting all Shared Records

    When true, the includeAllWriters flag indicates that results should include all records shared with the client making the query request.

    • Field Detail

      • nextToken

        public final long nextToken
        By default nextToken should be 0 for the first request of a search. For subsequent requests of the same search, it should be set to the SearchResponse#last() value.

      • limit

        public final int limit
        The maximum number of records to return. If 0, uses the server default of 50. Maximum page size is limited to 1000

      • includeAllWriters

        public final boolean includeAllWriters
        If true, include all records shared with this client. Otherwise only includes records written by this client.

      • includeData

        public final boolean includeData
        If true, include record data with results. Otherwise, only include metadata.

        When this value is true, then Record.data() will contain the record's unencrypted data. If false data() will return an empty Map.

        In either case, Record.meta() will always return metadata about the record.

      • match

        public List<SearchRequest.SearchParams> match
        A list of SearchParam that are logically ORed together and any matching record is returned. If no items are provided all records will match.

        exclude supersedes match, such that if match and exclude associate the same record it will not be returned

      • exclude

        public List<SearchRequest.SearchParams> exclude
        A list of SearchParam that are logically ORed together and any non-matching record returned.

        exclude supersedes match, such that if match and exclude associate the same record it will not be returned

      • range

        public final SearchRequest.SearchRange range
        If not null only records within the provided SearchRequest.SearchRange will be returned.

      • order

        public final SearchRequest.SearchOrder order
        If not null returns the records ordered as specified by the provided SearchRequest.SearchOrder.

        If null results are returned in ascending order by rec
